  <arm_group>
    <arm_group_label>Abatacept in combination with methotrexate</arm_group_label>
    <arm_group_type>Experimental</arm_group_type>
    <description>Abatacept subcutaneous (SC) injection, 125 mg, weekly for 24 weeks. Methotrexate (MTX) for at least 12 weeks prior to randomization with a stable oral dose for at least 4 weeks, Subjects must randomize on the maximum tolerated dose of oral methotrexate (minimum of 15 mg and maximum of 25 mg per week), dose of MTX &lt; 15 mg/week but ≥ 7.5 mg/week is permitted if subjects are intolerant to higher doses. Open-label Abatacept subcutaneous (SC) injection, 125 mg, weekly and maintain the enrollment dose of MTX unless toxicity or intolerability occurs during the study.</description>
  </arm_group>
  <arm_group>
    <arm_group_label>Adalimumab in combination with methotrexate</arm_group_label>
    <arm_group_type>Active Comparator</arm_group_type>
    <description>Adalimumab SC injection, 40 mg, once every two weeks for 24 weeks, Methotrexate (MTX) for at least 12 weeks prior to randomization with a stable oral dose for at least 4 weeks, Subjects must randomize on the maximum tolerated dose of oral methotrexate (minimum of 15 mg and maximum of 25 mg per week), dose of MTX &lt; 15 mg/week but ≥ 7.5 mg/week is permitted if subjects are intolerant to higher doses. Open-label Abatacept subcutaneous (SC) injection, 125 mg, weekly and maintain the enrollment dose of MTX unless toxicity or intolerability occurs during the study.</description>
  </arm_group>
